Summary

Confirmed the event-log RPC issue still existed in HEAD and fixed it by threading the authenticated EventLog.Identity into post-auth write/change callbacks, so handlers no longer rely on request-controlled publicKey values after authentication.

Added a shared Changes guard that rejects requests whose payload publicKey differs from the authenticated session identity with a Forbidden EventLogProtocolError.

Updated encrypted event-log writes and change streams to reject mismatched write payloads and derive storage access from the authenticated identity.

Updated unencrypted authentication to apply authorizeIdentity, and updated unencrypted writes/reads to authorize, map, process, and provide handler identity using the authenticated identity instead of the request payload public key.

Added regression tests for cross-identity unencrypted write spoofing and encrypted Changes spoofing through the real RPC authentication flow.

Added an Effect patch changeset for the runtime security behavior change.

Committed changes on the current branch with commit c68e2e41 and created the PR record.

